         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Easter-sunday 1878. ¶  ¶ Strange to say, dear Mr Ramsay, the few Glumaceae from N.Z. cannot be found; ¶  they are evidently mislaid, though I keep the N.Z plants separate in my Museum. I have sacrific...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">78.04.21</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Edward Ramsay</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">ML MSS.562, Letters to E. P. Ramsay 1862-91, Mitchell Library, State Library of New South Wales, Sydney.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">Easter-sunday 1878.<note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Easter fell on 21 April in 1878.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Strange to say, dear Mr Ramsay, the few <name key="Glumaceae">Glumaceae</name> from N.Z. cannot be found;<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See M to E. Ramsay, 4 April and 14 April 1878.</p>
               </note> they are evidently mislaid, though I keep the N.Z plants separate in my Museum. I have sacrificed some time in searching for these specimens, but in vain. This mishap is excusable, when I say, that to the only room for my museum plants (i.e. my museum) has not been added since 21 years. Want of space causes much confusion. Pray send me the names of the missing <name key="Glumaceae">Glumaceae</name>, and I will pick out <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">better</hi>
               </seg> specimens for your trustee from my normal collection at once then.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Regardfully</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd von Mueller</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Glumaceae">Glumaceae</name>
            </p>
